AZq_SBJsqsleJkQCksYsjg
This review is a little bit late, but I still dream about the Scottsdale Resort as if we stayed there just yesterday.  Our room was absolutely GORGEOUS and huge. We had a view of the golf course, and one night we even went outside to watch a late-night fireworks show over the course.  Our bathroom was also giant, and beautiful.  Beds were comfortable, pool was wonderful, and the  pool-side bar was great too.  We have recommended this hotel to several of our friends who have enjoyed it as well.  The only reason it doesn't get 5 stars from me is just simply because we didn't feel like the staff did anything "spectacular" for us, and frankly I don't even remember any of the staffers, which usually means (for me) that they were just average.

